6701522Di2015UniqueSeparator/// <summary>Di2015NewLine/// Provides conversion between long integers and custom number bases.Di2015NewLine/// </summary>Di2015NewLinepublic class BaseConverterDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    private string _characterSet;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Creates a new BaseConverter.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="characterSet">The characters in the custom base, in  Di2015NewLine    /// increasing order of value.</param>Di2015NewLine    public BaseConverter(string characterSet = Di2015NewLine       "0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz")Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        _characterSet = characterSet;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Converts a number in the custom base system to a long.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="value">The custom base number to convert.</param>Di2015NewLine    /// <returns>The long form of the custom base number.</returns>Di2015NewLine    public long StringToLong(string value)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (value == Convert.ToString(_characterSet[0])) return 0;Di2015NewLine        long val = 0; Di2015NewLine        string text = value[0] == '-' ? value.Substring(1, Di2015NewLine           value.Length - 1) : value;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for (int i = text.Length, power = 0; i != 0; i--, power++)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            val += (long)Math.Round((_characterSet.IndexOf(text[i-1]) * Di2015NewLine               Math.Pow(_characterSet.Length, power)));Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return value[0] == '-' ? -val : val;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Converts a long to the custom base system.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="value">The long to convert.</param>Di2015NewLine    /// <returns>The custome base number version of the long.</returns>Di2015NewLine    public string LongToString(long value)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (value == 0) return Convert.ToString(_characterSet[0]);Di2015NewLine        long number = value.Abs();Di2015NewLine        int remainder;Di2015NewLine        StringBuilder text = new StringBuilder((int)Math.Round(Di2015NewLine           Math.Log(long.MaxValue, (double)_characterSet.Length)) + Di2015NewLine           value < 0 ? 1 : 0);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        while (number != 0)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            remainder = (int)(number % _characterSet.Length);Di2015NewLine            text.Insert(0, _characterSet[remainder]);Di2015NewLine            number -= remainder;Di2015NewLine            number /= _characterSet.Length;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (value < 0) text.Insert(0, "-");Di2015NewLine        return text.ToString();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine

6723505Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static void NumericalSort(string[] ar)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    Regex rgx = new Regex("([^0-9]*)([0-9]+)");Di2015NewLine    Array.Sort(ar, (a, b) =>Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        var ma = rgx.Matches(a);Di2015NewLine        var mb = rgx.Matches(b);Di2015NewLine        for (int i = 0; i < ma.Count; ++i)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            int ret = ma[i].Groups[1].Value.CompareTo(mb[i].Groups[1].Value);Di2015NewLine            if (ret != 0)Di2015NewLine                return ret;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            ret = int.Parse(ma[i].Groups[2].Value) - int.Parse(mb[i].Groups[2].Value);Di2015NewLine            if (ret != 0)Di2015NewLine                return ret;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return 0;Di2015NewLine    });Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinestatic void Main(string[] args)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    string[] ar = new string[] { "a99.txt", "b98.txt", "b100.txt" };Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    NumericalSort(ar);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    foreach (var a in ar)Di2015NewLine        Console.WriteLine(a);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6724372Di2015UniqueSeparatorconvexHull
6724372Di2015UniqueSeparator// C-safe struct.Di2015NewLinestruct ResultsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    Point *points;Di2015NewLine    std::size_t num_points;Di2015NewLine};Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Store the real results in a vector, but derive from the C-safe struct.Di2015NewLinestruct ResultsImpl : ResultsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    Points storage;Di2015NewLine};Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// convexHull has been refactored to take pointersDi2015NewLine// instead of vector iterators.Di2015NewLineOutputIterator convexHull(Point const *first, Point const *last,Di2015NewLine    OutputIterator result);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// The exported function is callable from C.Di2015NewLine// It returns a C-safe Results, not ResultsImpl.Di2015NewLineextern "C" DLLEXPORT Results* convexHullC(Point const *points,Di2015NewLine                                          std::size_t num_points)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    tryDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        std::unique_ptr<ResultsImpl> r(new ResultImpl);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // fill in r->storage.Di2015NewLine        convexHull(points, points + num_points,Di2015NewLine            std::back_inserter(r->storage));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // fill in C-safe members.Di2015NewLine        r->points = &r->storage[0];Di2015NewLine        r->numPoints = &r->storage.size();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return r.release();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    catch(...)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // trap all exceptions!Di2015NewLine        return 0;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// needs to be called from C# to clean up the results.Di2015NewLineextern "C" DLLEXPORT void freeConvexHullC(Results *r)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    tryDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        delete (ResultsImpl*)r;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    catch(...)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // trap all exceptions!Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine
6724372Di2015UniqueSeparator[StructLayout(LayoutKind.Sequential)]Di2015NewLinestruct PointDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    double x;Di2015NewLine    double y;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine[StructLayout(LayoutKind.Sequential)]Di2015NewLinestruct ResultsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    IntPtr points;Di2015NewLine    IntPtr num_points;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine[DllImport("unmanagedCode")]Di2015NewLineIntPtr convexHullC(Point[] points, IntPtr pointCount);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine[DllImport("unmanagedCode")]Di2015NewLinevoid freeConvexHullC(IntPtr results);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinePoint[] ConvexHull(Point[] points)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    IntPtr pr = convexHull(points, new IntPtr(points.Length));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if(pr == IntPtr.Zero)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throw new Exception("native error!");Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    tryDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        Results r = Marshal.PtrToStructure(pr, typeof(Results));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        points = new Point[checked((int)(long)r.num_points)];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for(int i = 0; i < points.Length; ++i)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            points[i] = Marshal.PtrToStructure(Di2015NewLine                r.points + Marshal.Sizeof(typeof(Point)) * i,Di2015NewLine                typeof(Point));Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return points;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    finallyDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        freeConvexHull(pr);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6734687Di2015UniqueSeparatordbo.StringToNumSet()
6734687Di2015UniqueSeparatorCREATE FUNCTION [dbo].[StringToNumSet] (Di2015NewLine @TargetString  varchar(MAX),Di2015NewLine @SearchChar varchar(1)Di2015NewLine )Di2015NewLineRETURNS @Set TABLE (Di2015NewLine num int not nullDi2015NewLine )Di2015NewLineASDi2015NewLineBEGINDi2015NewLine DECLARE @SearchCharPos  int,  @LastSearchCharPos intDi2015NewLine SET @SearchCharPos = 0Di2015NewLine WHILE 1=1Di2015NewLine BEGINDi2015NewLine  SET @LastSearchCharPos = @SearchCharPosDi2015NewLine  SET @SearchCharPos = CHARINDEX( @SearchChar, @TargetString, @SearchCharPos + 1 )Di2015NewLine  IF @SearchCharPos = 0Di2015NewLine  BEGINDi2015NewLine   INSERT @Set( num ) VALUES ( SUBSTRING( @TargetString, @LastSearchCharPos + 1, DATALENGTH( @TargetString ) ) )Di2015NewLine   BREAKDi2015NewLine  ENDDi2015NewLine  ELSEDi2015NewLine   INSERT @Set( num ) VALUES ( SUBSTRING( @TargetString, @LastSearchCharPos + 1, @SearchCharPos - @LastSearchCharPos - 1 ) )Di2015NewLine ENDDi2015NewLine RETURNDi2015NewLineENDDi2015NewLine

6751918Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static class ExtensionsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    public static IEnumerable<T> ReplaceSequence<T>(this IEnumerable<T> original, IEnumerable<T> toSearch, IEnumerable<T> toReplace) where T : IEquatable<T>Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        T[] toSearchItems = toSearch.ToArray();Di2015NewLine        List<T> window = new List<T>();Di2015NewLine        foreach (T value in original)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            window.Add(value);Di2015NewLine            if (window.Count == toSearchItems.Length)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                bool match = true;Di2015NewLine                for (int i = 0; i < toSearchItems.Length; i++)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    if (!toSearchItems[i].Equals(window[i]))Di2015NewLine                    {Di2015NewLine                        match = false;Di2015NewLine                        break;Di2015NewLine                    }Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                if (match)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    foreach (T toReplaceValue in toReplace)Di2015NewLine                    {Di2015NewLine                        yield return toReplaceValue;Di2015NewLine                    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    window.Clear();Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                elseDi2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    yield return window[0];Di2015NewLine                    window.RemoveAt(0);Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        foreach (T value in window)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            yield return value;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine// http://stackoverflow.com/q/6751533/751090Di2015NewLinepublic class StackOverflow_6751533Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    public static void Test()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        byte[] byteArray = new byte[] { 0x01, 0x02, 0x7E, 0x7E, 0x04 };Di2015NewLine        byte[] escapeSequence = new byte[] { 0x7E, 0x7E };Di2015NewLine        byte[] unescapedSequence = new byte[] { 0x7E };Di2015NewLine        byte[] outputBytes = byteArray.ReplaceSequence(escapeSequence, unescapedSequence).ToArray();Di2015NewLine        for (int i = 0; i < outputBytes.Length; i++)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            Console.Write("{0:X2} ", (int)outputBytes[i]);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        Console.WriteLine();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

  var itemContainer = (ListBoxItem)listBox.ItemContainerGenerator.ContainerFromItem(item);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            if (WPFHelpers.IsObjectVisibleInContainer(itemContainer, listBox) == }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic enum ControlVisibilityDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    Hidden,Di2015NewLine    Partial,Di2015NewLine    Full,Di2015NewLine    FullHeightPartialWidth,Di2015NewLine    FullWidthPartialHeightDi2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic class WPFHelpersDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Checks to see if an object is rendered visible within a parent containerDi2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="child">UI element of child object</param>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="parent">UI Element of parent object</param>Di2015NewLine    /// <returns>ControlVisibility Enum: Hidden, Partial or Visible</returns>Di2015NewLine    public static ControlVisibility IsObjectVisibleInContainer(FrameworkElement child, UIElement parent)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        GeneralTransform childTransform = child.TransformToAncestor(parent);Di2015NewLine        //Rect childSize = childTransform.TransformBounds(new Rect(new Point(0, 0), child.RenderSize));Di2015NewLine        Rect childSize = childTransform.TransformBounds(new Rect(new Point(0, 0), new Point(child.ActualWidth, child.ActualHeight)));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        Rect result = Rect.Intersect(new Rect(new Point(0, 0), parent.RenderSize), childSize);Di2015NewLine        if (result == Rect.Empty)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            return ControlVisibility.Hidden;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        if (result.Height == childSize.Height && result.Width == childSize.Width)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            return ControlVisibility.Full;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        if (result.Height == childSize.Height)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            return ControlVisibility.FullHeightPartialWidth;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        if (result.Width == childSize.Width)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            return ControlVisibility.FullWidthPartialHeight;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        return ControlVisibility.Partial;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine/// <summary>Di2015NewLine/// Class implementing helpful extensions to ListBox.Di2015NewLine/// </summary>Di2015NewLinepublic static class ListBoxExtensionsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Causes the object to scroll into view centered.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="listBox">ListBox instance.</param>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="item">Object to scroll.</param>Di2015NewLine    //[SuppressMessage("Microsoft.Design", "CA1011:ConsiderPassingBaseTypesAsParameters",Di2015NewLine    //    Justification = "Deliberately targeting ListBox.")]Di2015NewLine    public static void ScrollIntoViewTop(this ListBox listBox, object item)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        Debug.Assert(!VirtualizingStackPanel.GetIsVirtualizing(listBox),Di2015NewLine            "VirtualizingStackPanel.IsVirtualizing must be disabled for ScrollIntoViewCentered to work.");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Get the container for the specified itemDi2015NewLine        var container = listBox.ItemContainerGenerator.ContainerFromItem(item) as FrameworkElement;Di2015NewLine        if (null != container)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            if (ScrollViewer.GetCanContentScroll(listBox))Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                // Get the parent IScrollInfoDi2015NewLine                var scrollInfo = VisualTreeHelper.GetParent(container) as IScrollInfo;Di2015NewLine                if (null != scrollInfo)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    // Need to know orientation, so parent must be a known typeDi2015NewLine                    var stackPanel = scrollInfo as StackPanel;Di2015NewLine                    var virtualizingStackPanel = scrollInfo as VirtualizingStackPanel;Di2015NewLine                    Debug.Assert((null != stackPanel) || (null != virtualizingStackPanel),Di2015NewLine                        "ItemsPanel must be a StackPanel or VirtualizingStackPanel for ScrollIntoViewCentered to work.");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    // Get the container's indexDi2015NewLine                    var index = listBox.ItemContainerGenerator.IndexFromContainer(container);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    // Center the item by splitting the extra spaceDi2015NewLine                    if (((null != stackPanel) && (Orientation.Horizontal == stackPanel.Orientation)) ||Di2015NewLine                        ((null != virtualizingStackPanel) && (Orientation.Horizontal == virtualizingStackPanel.Orientation)))Di2015NewLine                    {Di2015NewLine                        //scrollInfo.SetHorizontalOffset(index - Math.Floor(scrollInfo.ViewportWidth / 2));Di2015NewLine                        scrollInfo.SetHorizontalOffset(index);Di2015NewLine                    }Di2015NewLine                    elseDi2015NewLine                    {Di2015NewLine                        //scrollInfo.SetVerticalOffset(index - Math.Floor(scrollInfo.ViewportHeight / 2));Di2015NewLine                        scrollInfo.SetVerticalOffset(index);Di2015NewLine                    }Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            elseDi2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                // Get the bounds of the item containerDi2015NewLine                var rect = new Rect(new Point(), container.RenderSize);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                // Find constraining parent (either the nearest ScrollContentPresenter or the ListBox itself)Di2015NewLine                FrameworkElement constrainingParent = container;Di2015NewLine                doDi2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    constrainingParent = VisualTreeHelper.GetParent(constrainingParent) as FrameworkElement;Di2015NewLine                } while ((null != constrainingParent) &&Di2015NewLine                         (listBox != constrainingParent) &&Di2015NewLine                         !(constrainingParent is ScrollContentPresenter));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                if (null != constrainingParent)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    // Inflate rect to fill the constraining parentDi2015NewLine                    rect.Inflate(Di2015NewLine                        Math.Max((constrainingParent.ActualWidth - rect.Width) / 2, 0),Di2015NewLine                        Math.Max((constrainingParent.ActualHeight - rect.Height) / 2, 0));Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                // Bring the (inflated) bounds into viewDi2015NewLine                container.BringIntoView(rect);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6808956Di2015UniqueSeparatorclass BoxFinder {Di2015NewLine    class Range {Di2015NewLine        public Range(int startX, int startY, int endY) {Di2015NewLine            StartX = startX;Di2015NewLine            StartY = startY;Di2015NewLine            EndY = endY;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        public int StartX { get; private set; }Di2015NewLine        public int StartY { get; private set; }Di2015NewLine        public int EndY { get; private set; }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    public BoxFinder(int[,] data) {Di2015NewLine        Data = data;Di2015NewLine        Width = data.GetLength(0);Di2015NewLine        Height = data.GetLength(1);Di2015NewLine        ranges = new Range[Height];Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public int[,] Data { get; private set; }Di2015NewLine    public int Width { get; private set; }Di2015NewLine    public int Height { get; private set; }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private Range[] ranges;Di2015NewLine    public IEnumerable<Rectangle> GetBoxes() {Di2015NewLine        for (int x = 0; x < Width; x++) {Di2015NewLine            Range currentRange = null;Di2015NewLine            for (int y = 0; y < Height; y++) {Di2015NewLine                Func<Range, Rectangle> CloseRange = r => {Di2015NewLine                    currentRange = null;Di2015NewLine                    ranges[r.StartY] = null;Di2015NewLine                    return new Rectangle(Di2015NewLine                        r.StartY,Di2015NewLine                        r.StartX,Di2015NewLine                        x - r.StartX,Di2015NewLine                        r.EndY - r.StartYDi2015NewLine                    );Di2015NewLine                };Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                if (currentRange == null || currentRange.EndY <= y)Di2015NewLine                    currentRange = ranges[y];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                if (Data[x, y] == 1) {Di2015NewLine                    if (currentRange == null) {Di2015NewLine                        int startY = y;Di2015NewLine                        for (; y < Height && Data[x, y] == 1; y++) {Di2015NewLine                            if (ranges[y] != null)Di2015NewLine                                yield return CloseRange(ranges[y]);Di2015NewLine                            //If there are fuzzy edges, break; insteadDi2015NewLine                        }Di2015NewLine                        ranges[startY] = new Range(x, startY, y);Di2015NewLine                        if (y == Height)Di2015NewLine                            continue;Di2015NewLine                        //Otherwise, continue to the next if in case a previous range just endedDi2015NewLine                    }Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                //No else; we can get here after creating a rangeDi2015NewLine                if(Data[x, y] == 0) {Di2015NewLine                    if (currentRange != null)Di2015NewLine                        yield return CloseRange(currentRange);Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6813538Di2015UniqueSeparatorvar data = Expression.Parameter(typeof (float[][]));Di2015NewLinevar n = Expression.Parameter(typeof (int));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinevar body = Di2015NewLine    Expression.Multiply( // *Di2015NewLine        Expression.Add( // +Di2015NewLine            Expression.ArrayIndex(Di2015NewLine                Expression.ArrayIndex(data, Expression.Constant(0)), n), // a[n]Di2015NewLine            Expression.ArrayIndex(Di2015NewLine                Expression.ArrayIndex(data, Expression.Constant(1)), n) // b[n]Di2015NewLine            ),Di2015NewLine        Expression.ArrayIndex(Di2015NewLine            Expression.ArrayIndex(data, Expression.Constant(2)), n)  // c[n]Di2015NewLine    );Di2015NewLinevar func = Expression.Lambda<Func<float[][], int, float>>(body, data, n).Compile();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// here, a===jagged[0], b===jagged[1], c===jagged[2]Di2015NewLinefloat[][] jagged = new[] { new[] { 1F, 2F }, new[] { 3F, 4F }, new[] { 5F, 6F } };Di2015NewLinefor(int i = 0; i < 2; i++)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    Console.WriteLine("{0}: {1}", i, func(jagged, i));Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6813883Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic class MapDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine     public MapPoint[,] mapPoints;       //the mapDi2015NewLine     public Player player;               //the player/user objectDi2015NewLine     public Vector2 DrawHeroPosition;    Di2015NewLine     //where at the screen the player is going to be drawnDi2015NewLine     public Vector2 RangeStart;          Di2015NewLine     //what part of the map who is going to be drawnDi2015NewLine     public int SizeX;     //number of mapPoints the screen can contain at one time Di2015NewLine     public int SizeY;     //number of mapPoints the screen can contain at one time Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine     //MapPoint represents a specific 512x512 point (mapPoint) its position atDi2015NewLine     //the map but also includes the sprite that is going to be drawn and objectsDi2015NewLine     //that the player can interact with at that place (like the door)Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine     //the player object includes reference to where in the world it is placeDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine     public Map(ContentManager theContentManager, int x, int y)Di2015NewLine     {Di2015NewLine        MapSizeX = x;Di2015NewLine        MapSizeY = y;Di2015NewLine        int ScreenSizeX = 9;Di2015NewLine        int ScreenSizeY = 9;Di2015NewLine        mapPoints = new MapPoint[MapSizeX , MapSizeY];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //ad code for generating/creating map...Di2015NewLine        //important that you store the MapPoints position inside each mapPointDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        player = new Player(mapPoints[0,0]);  //crate a player who knows where he isDi2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public void Update()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine       //in the update method you do a lot of things like movement and soDi2015NewLine       //set what part of the map the game should draw if the game for exampleDi2015NewLine       //can show 9x9 512points at a single timeDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine       //give range value from the players positionDi2015NewLine        RangeStart.X = player.PositionX;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //test if the maps position is in the left corner of the mapDi2015NewLine        //if it is draw the map from the start..(RangeStart.X = 0)Di2015NewLine        if (player.PositionX - (ScreenSizeX / 2) < 0) { RangeStart.X = 0; }Di2015NewLine        //if not draw the hero in the mitle of the screenDi2015NewLine        elseDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            RangeStart.X = player.PositionX - (ScreenSizeX / 2);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        //if the hero is in the right corer, fix his positionDi2015NewLine        while (RangeStart.X + ScreenSizeX > MapSizeX)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            RangeStart.X--;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //the same thing for the Y axleDi2015NewLine        RangeStart.Y = player.PositionY;Di2015NewLine        if (player.PositionY - (ScreenSizeY / 2) < 0) { RangeStart.Y = 0; }Di2015NewLine        elseDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            RangeStart.Y = player.PositionY - (ScreenSizeY / 2);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        while (RangeStart.Y + ScreenSizeY > MapSizeY)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            RangeStart.Y--;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //time to set the position of the hero...Di2015NewLine        //he works like the opposite of the range, if you move what part of the mapDi2015NewLine        //you draw you dont change the heros draw position, if you dont move the rangeDi2015NewLine        //you have to move the hero to create the illusion of "moment"Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //if you are in the left part you have to move the heros draw position..Di2015NewLine        if (player.PositionX - (ScreenSizeX / 2) < 0) Di2015NewLine        { DrawHeroPosition.X = player.PositionX; }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //if you are in the right partDi2015NewLine        else if (player.PositionX+1 > MapSizeX - (ScreenSizeX / 2))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            DrawHeroPosition.X = player.PositionX - (MapSizeX - ScreenSizeX);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //if you aint in a corner, just place the hero in the middle of the mapDi2015NewLine        elseDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            DrawHeroPosition.X = (ScreenSizeX / 2);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //the same thing for YDi2015NewLine        if (player.PositionY - (ScreenSizeY / 2) < 0) Di2015NewLine        { DrawHeroPosition.Y = player.PositionY; }Di2015NewLine        else if (player.PositionY+1 > MapSizeY - (ScreenSizeY / 2))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            DrawHeroPosition.Y = player.PositionY - (MapSizeY - ScreenSizeY);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        elseDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            DrawHeroPosition.Y = (ScreenSizeY / 2);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public void Draw()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        int x = (int)RangeStart.X;Di2015NewLine        int y = (int)RangeStart.Y;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for(int counterX = 0; x < ((MapSizeX)); x++, counterX++)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            for (int counterY = 0; y < (MapSizeY); y++, counterY++)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine               if (mapPoints[x, y] != null)Di2015NewLine               {Di2015NewLine                 mapPoints[x, y].Draw(spriteBatch, mapPoints[counterX,counterY].positonInMatrix);Di2015NewLine                 //mapPoints[counterX,counterY] = where to drawDi2015NewLine                 //mapPoints[x, y] = what to drawDi2015NewLine               }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            y = (int)RangeStart.Y;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6814291Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate static TimeSpan FindOverlap(ParkingTime parkingTime, TimeZone timeZone)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    // Handle wraparound zones like 23-6. Note that this doesn't attemptDi2015NewLine    // to handle *parking* which starts at 11.30pm etc.Di2015NewLine    if (timeZone.Start > timeZone.End)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return FindOverlap(parkingTime,Di2015NewLine                     new TimeZone(timeZone.Start.Date, timeZone.End)Di2015NewLine             + FindOverlap(parkingTime,Di2015NewLine                     new TimeZone(timeZone.End, timeZone.Start.Date.AddDays(1));Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    DateTime overlapStart = Max(parkingTime.Start, timeZone.Start);Di2015NewLine    DateTime overlapEnd = Min(parkingTime.End, timeZone.End);Di2015NewLine    TimeSpan overlap = overlapEnd - overlapStart;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // If the customer arrived after the end or left before the start,Di2015NewLine    // the overlap will be negative at this point.Di2015NewLine    return overlap < TimeSpan.Zero ? TimeSpan.Zero : overlap;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineprivate static DateTime Min(DateTime x, DateTime y)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    return x < y ? x : y;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineprivate static DateTime Max(DateTime x, DateTime y)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    return x > y ? x : y;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

I prefer to leave it outDi2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    context.Response.Write(e.Data);Di2015NewLine                    context.Response.Write(Environment.NewLine);Di2015NewLine                    context.Response.Flush();Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            });Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            process.OutputDataReceived += new DataReceivedEventHandler(dataReceived);Di2015NewLine            process.ErrorDataReceived += new DataReceivedEventHandler(dataReceived);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // use text/plain so line breaks and any other whitespace formatting is preservedDi2015NewLine            context.Response.ContentType = "text/plain";Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // start the process and start reading the standard and error outputsDi2015NewLine            process.Start();Di2015NewLine            process.BeginErrorReadLine();Di2015NewLine            process.BeginOutputReadLine();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // wait for the process to exitDi2015NewLine            process.WaitForExit();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // an exit code other than 0 generally means an errorDi2015NewLine            if (process.ExitCode != 0)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                context.Response.StatusCode = 500;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    #endregionDi2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6837737Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate static void SortRichTextBox(RichTextBox richTextBox)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    var lineArray = richTextBox.Lines;Di2015NewLine    Array.Sort(lineArray, delegate(string a, string b)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // I omitted Important corner cases like malformed lines,Di2015NewLine        // empty strings, and nulls.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Additional sort cases can be added to the array as needed.Di2015NewLine        var sortOrder = new[] { "1111", "2222", "4444", "9999", "DDDD" };Di2015NewLine        var aTokens = a.Split(new[] { ' ' }, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries);Di2015NewLine        var bTokens = b.Split(new[] { ' ' }, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        var aSignifier = Array.FindIndex(sortOrder, item => aTokens[5].Contains(item));Di2015NewLine        var bSignifier = Array.FindIndex(sortOrder, item => bTokens[5].Contains(item));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // This is where your first rule is being implemented, based on the dataDi2015NewLine        // from the last column.  The math is unimportant, what matters is the Di2015NewLine        // return being positive vs. negative vs. zero.Di2015NewLine        if (aSignifier != bSignifier)Di2015NewLine            return aSignifier - bSignifier;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // This is where your second rule is being implemented, as a backup whenDi2015NewLine        // the result from the first rule indicates equality.  We're just fallingDi2015NewLine        // through to ordinary string comparison on the second column.Di2015NewLine        return aTokens[1].CompareTo(bTokens[1]);Di2015NewLine    });Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // We want to call the setter to get the textbox to update.Di2015NewLine    richTextBox.Lines = lineArray;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6851633Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static void RemoveWithNextWhitespace(this XElement element)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    IEnumerable<XText> textNodesDi2015NewLine        = element.NodesAfterSelf()Di2015NewLine                 .TakeWhile(node => node is XText).Cast<XText>();Di2015NewLine    if (element.ElementsAfterSelf().Any()) {Di2015NewLine        // Easy case, remove following text nodes.Di2015NewLine        textNodes.ToList().ForEach(node => node.Remove());Di2015NewLine    } else {Di2015NewLine        // Remove trailing whitespace.Di2015NewLine        textNodes.TakeWhile(text => !text.Value.Contains("\\n"))Di2015NewLine                 .ToList().ForEach(text => text.Remove());Di2015NewLine        // Fetch text node containing newline, if any.Di2015NewLine        XText newLineTextNodeDi2015NewLine            = element.NodesAfterSelf().OfType<XText>().FirstOrDefault();Di2015NewLine        if (newLineTextNode != null) {Di2015NewLine            string value = newLineTextNode.Value;Di2015NewLine            if (value.Length > 1) {Di2015NewLine                // Composite text node, trim until newline (inclusive).Di2015NewLine                newLineTextNode.AddAfterSelf(Di2015NewLine                    new XText(value.SubString(value.IndexOf('\\n') + 1)));Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            // Remove original node.Di2015NewLine            newLineTextNode.Remove();Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    element.Remove();Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6852712Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static class RuntimeExtensionsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine   public static WriteableBitmap CreateLivePlayerRenderer(this Runtime runtime)Di2015NewLine   {Di2015NewLine      if (runtime.DepthStream.Width == 0)Di2015NewLine         throw new InvalidOperationException("Either open the depth stream before calling this method or use the overload which takes in the resolution that the depth stream will later be opened with.");Di2015NewLine      return runtime.CreateLivePlayerRenderer(runtime.DepthStream.Width, runtime.DepthStream.Height);Di2015NewLine   }Di2015NewLine   public static WriteableBitmap CreateLivePlayerRenderer(this Runtime runtime, int depthWidth, int depthHeight)Di2015NewLine   {Di2015NewLine      PlanarImage depthImage = new PlanarImage();Di2015NewLine      WriteableBitmap target = new WriteableBitmap(depthWidth, depthHeight, 96, 96, PixelFormats.Bgra32, null);Di2015NewLine      var depthRect = new System.Windows.Int32Rect(0, 0, depthWidth, depthHeight);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      runtime.DepthFrameReady += (s, e) =>Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                depthImage = e.ImageFrame.Image;Di2015NewLine                Debug.Assert(depthImage.Height == depthHeight && depthImage.Width == depthWidth);Di2015NewLine            };Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      runtime.VideoFrameReady += (s, e) =>Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                // don't do anything if we don't yet have a depth imageDi2015NewLine                if (depthImage.Bits == null) return;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                byte[] color = e.ImageFrame.Image.Bits;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                byte[] output = new byte[depthWidth * depthHeight * 4];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                // loop over each pixel in the depth imageDi2015NewLine                int outputIndex = 0;Di2015NewLine                for (int depthY = 0, depthIndex = 0; depthY < depthHeight; depthY++)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    for (int depthX = 0; depthX < depthWidth; depthX++, depthIndex += 2)Di2015NewLine                    {Di2015NewLine                        // combine the 2 bytes of depth data representing this pixelDi2015NewLine                        short depthValue = (short)(depthImage.Bits[depthIndex] | (depthImage.Bits[depthIndex + 1] << 8));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                        // extract the id of a tracked player from the first bit of depth data for this pixelDi2015NewLine                        int player = depthImage.Bits[depthIndex] & 7;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                        // find a pixel in the color image which matches this coordinate from the depth imageDi2015NewLine                        int colorX, colorY;Di2015NewLine                        runtime.NuiCamera.GetColorPixelCoordinatesFromDepthPixel(Di2015NewLine                            e.ImageFrame.Resolution,Di2015NewLine                            e.ImageFrame.ViewArea,Di2015NewLine                            depthX, depthY, // depth coordinateDi2015NewLine                            depthValue,  // depth valueDi2015NewLine                            out colorX, out colorY);  // color coordinateDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                        // ensure that the calculated color location is within the bounds of the imageDi2015NewLine                        colorX = Math.Max(0, Math.Min(colorX, e.ImageFrame.Image.Width - 1));Di2015NewLine                        colorY = Math.Max(0, Math.Min(colorY, e.ImageFrame.Image.Height - 1));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                        output[outputIndex++] = color[(4 * (colorX + (colorY * e.ImageFrame.Image.Width))) + 0];Di2015NewLine                        output[outputIndex++] = color[(4 * (colorX + (colorY * e.ImageFrame.Image.Width))) + 1];Di2015NewLine                        output[outputIndex++] = color[(4 * (colorX + (colorY * e.ImageFrame.Image.Width))) + 2];Di2015NewLine                        output[outputIndex++] = player > 0 ? (byte)255 : (byte)0;Di2015NewLine                    }Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                target.WritePixels(depthRect, output, depthWidth * PixelFormats.Bgra32.BitsPerPixel / 8, 0);Di2015NewLine            };Di2015NewLine            return target;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine

6855438Di2015UniqueSeparatornnoremap <buffer> ]m :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('{', 'W',  'n')<cr>Di2015NewLinennoremap <buffer> [m :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('{', 'Wb', 'n')<cr>Di2015NewLinennoremap <buffer> ]M :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('}', 'W',  'n')<cr>Di2015NewLinennoremap <buffer> [M :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('}', 'Wb', 'n')<cr>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinexnoremap <buffer> ]m :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('{', 'W',  'v')<cr>Di2015NewLinexnoremap <buffer> [m :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('{', 'Wb', 'v')<cr>Di2015NewLinexnoremap <buffer> ]M :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('}', 'W',  'v')<cr>Di2015NewLinexnoremap <buffer> [M :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('}', 'Wb', 'v')<cr>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineonoremap <buffer> ]m :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('{', 'W',  'o')<cr>Di2015NewLineonoremap <buffer> [m :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('{', 'Wb', 'o')<cr>Di2015NewLineonoremap <buffer> ]M :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('}', 'W',  'o')<cr>Di2015NewLineonoremap <buffer> [M :<c-u>call <SID>JumpMethod('}', 'Wb', 'o')<cr>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinefunction! s:JumpMethod(char, flags, mode)Di2015NewLine  let original_cursor = getpos('.')Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  if a:mode == 'v'Di2015NewLine    normal! gvDi2015NewLine  elseif a:mode == 'o'Di2015NewLine    normal! vDi2015NewLine  endifDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  while search(a:char, a:flags) > 0Di2015NewLine    if a:char == '}'Di2015NewLine      " jump to the opening one to analyze the definitionDi2015NewLine      normal! %Di2015NewLine    endifDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    let current_line = line('.')Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if getline(current_line) =~ '^\\s*{'Di2015NewLine      " it's alone on the line, check the above oneDi2015NewLine      let method_line = current_line - 1Di2015NewLine    elseDi2015NewLine      let method_line = current_lineDi2015NewLine    endifDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    let method_line_body = getline(method_line)Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if method_line_body =~ '\\k\\+\\s*(.*)' && method_line_body !~ '\\<\\(for\\|foreach\\|if\\|while\\|switch\\|using\\|catch\\|get\\|set\\)\\>'Di2015NewLine      " it's probably a function callDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      if a:char == '}'Di2015NewLine        " we need to go back to the closing bracketDi2015NewLine        normal! %Di2015NewLine      endifDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      echoDi2015NewLine      returnDi2015NewLine    elseDi2015NewLine      if a:char == '}'Di2015NewLine        " we still need to go back to the closing bracketDi2015NewLine        normal! %Di2015NewLine      endifDi2015NewLine    endifDi2015NewLine  endwhileDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  " if we're here, the search has failed, restore cursor positionDi2015NewLine  echoDi2015NewLine  call setpos('.', original_cursor)Di2015NewLineendfunctionDi2015NewLine

6866141Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate void BeginReceive()Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if ( _clientState == EClientState.Receiving)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (_asyncTask.BytesReceived != 0 && _asyncTask.TotalBytesReceived <= _maxPageSize)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            SocketAsyncEventArgs e = new SocketAsyncEventArgs();Di2015NewLine            e.SetBuffer(_asyncTask.ReceiveBuffer, 0, _asyncTask.ReceiveBuffer.Length);Di2015NewLine            e.Completed += new EventHandler<SocketAsyncEventArgs>(ReceiveCallback);Di2015NewLine            e.UserToken = _asyncTask.Host;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            bool comletedAsync = false;Di2015NewLine            tryDi2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                comletedAsync = _socket.ReceiveAsync(e);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            catch (SocketException se)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                Console.WriteLine("Error receiving data from: " + _asyncTask.Host);Di2015NewLine                Console.WriteLine("SocketException: {0} Error Code: {1}", se.Message, se.NativeErrorCode);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                ChangeState(EClientState.Failed);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            if (!comletedAsync)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                // The call completed synchronously so invoke the callback ourselvesDi2015NewLine                ReceiveCallback(this, e);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        elseDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            //Console.WriteLine("Num bytes received: " + _asyncTask.TotalBytesReceived);Di2015NewLine            ChangeState(EClientState.ReceiveDone);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine
6866141Di2015UniqueSeparatorBeginReceive
6866141Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate void ReceiveCallback(object sender, SocketAsyncEventArgs args)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    lock (_sync) // re-entrant lockDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // Fast fail: should not be receiving data if the clientDi2015NewLine        // is not in a receiving state.Di2015NewLine        if (_clientState == EClientState.Receiving)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            String host = (String)args.UserToken;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            if (_asyncTask.Host == host && args.SocketError == SocketError.Success)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                tryDi2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    Encoding encoding = Encoding.ASCII;Di2015NewLine                    _asyncTask.BytesReceived = args.BytesTransferred;Di2015NewLine                    _asyncTask.TotalBytesReceived += _asyncTask.BytesReceived;Di2015NewLine                    _asyncTask.DocSource += encoding.GetString(_asyncTask.ReceiveBuffer, 0, _asyncTask.BytesReceived);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    BeginReceive(); // <---- THIS IS WHAT YOU'RE MISSINGDi2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                catch (SocketException e)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    Console.WriteLine("Error receiving data from: " + host);Di2015NewLine                    Console.WriteLine("SocketException: {0} Error Code: {1}", e.Message, e.NativeErrorCode);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    ChangeState(EClientState.Failed);Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            else if (_asyncTask.Host != host)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                Console.WriteLine("Warning: received a callback for {0}, but the client is currently working on {1}.",Di2015NewLine                    host, _asyncTask.Host);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            elseDi2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                Console.WriteLine("Socket Error: {0} when receiving from {1}",Di2015NewLine                   args.SocketError,Di2015NewLine                   _asyncTask.Host);Di2015NewLine                ChangeState(EClientState.Failed);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

id)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    using(var connection = ConnectionFactory.Create())Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        using (var command = new SqlCommand("[dbo].[GetResponse]", connection))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            command.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            command.Parameters.Add("@Id", SqlDbType.UniqueIdentifier);Di2015NewLine            command.Parameters.AddReturnValue();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            command.Parameters["@Id"].Value = id;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine if(reader.Read())Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    WriteResponse(context, reader);Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine#endregionDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine#region WriteResponse(HttpContext context, SqlDataReader reader)Di2015NewLine/// <summary>Di2015NewLine/// Writes the content for a media resource to the response stream using the supplied <paramref name="reader"/>.Di2015NewLine/// </summary>Di2015NewLine/// <param name="context">The <see cref="HttpContext"/> to write content to.</param>Di2015NewLine/// <param name="reader">The <see cref="SqlDataReader"/> to extract information from.</param>Di2015NewLineprivate static void WriteResponse(HttpContext context, SqlDataReader reader)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if (context == null || reader == null)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    DateTime expiresOn      = DateTime.UtcNow;Di2015NewLine    string contentType      = String.Empty;Di2015NewLine    long contentLength      = 0;Di2015NewLine    string fileName         = String.Empty;Di2015NewLine    string fileExtension    = String.Empty;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    expiresOn               = reader.GetDateTime(0);Di2015NewLine    fileName                = reader.GetString(1);Di2015NewLine    fileExtension           = reader.GetString(2);Di2015NewLine    contentType             = reader.GetString(3);Di2015NewLine    contentLength           = reader.GetInt64(4);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    context.Response.AddHeader("Content-Disposition", String.Format(null, "attachment; filename={0}", fileName));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    WriteResponse(context, reader, contentType, contentLength);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    ApplyCachePolicy(context, expiresOn - DateTime.UtcNow);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine#endregionDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine#region WriteResponse(HttpContext context, SqlDataReader reader, string contentType, long contentLength)Di2015NewLine/// <summary>Di2015NewLine/// Writes the content for a media resource to the response stream using the Di2015NewLine/// specified reader, content type and content length.Di2015NewLine/// </summary>Di2015NewLine/// <param name="context">The <see cref="HttpContext"/> to write content to.</param>Di2015NewLine/// <param name="reader">The <see cref="SqlDataReader"/> to extract information from.</param>Di2015NewLine/// <param name="contentType">The content type of the media.</param>Di2015NewLine/// <param name="contentLength">The content length of the media.</param>Di2015NewLineprivate static void WriteResponse(HttpContext context, SqlDataReader reader, string contentType, long contentLength)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if (context == null || reader == null)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    int ordinal     = 5;Di2015NewLine    int bufferSize  = 4096 * 1024; // 4MBDi2015NewLine    byte[] buffer   = new byte[bufferSize];Di2015NewLine    long value;Di2015NewLine    long dataIndex;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    context.Response.Buffer         = false;Di2015NewLine    context.Response.ContentType    = contentType;Di2015NewLine    context.Response.AppendHeader("content-length", contentLength.ToString());Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    using (var writer = new BinaryWriter(context.Response.OutputStream))Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        dataIndex   = 0;Di2015NewLine        value       = reader.GetBytes(ordinal, dataIndex, buffer, 0, bufferSize);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        while(value == bufferSize)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            writer.Write(buffer);Di2015NewLine            writer.Flush();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            dataIndex   += bufferSize;Di2015NewLine            value       = reader.GetBytes(ordinal, dataIndex, buffer, 0, bufferSize);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        writer.Write(buffer, 0, (int)value);Di2015NewLine        writer.Flush();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine#endregionDi2015NewLine

6890312Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate List<string> GetStringCombinations(List<List<string>> collection)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLineList<string> ls = new List<string>();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// if the collection is empty, return null to stop the recursionDi2015NewLineif (!collection.Any())Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    return null;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine// recurse down the list, selecting one letter each timeDi2015NewLineelseDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    foreach (var letter in collection.First())Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // get the collection sans the first itemDi2015NewLine        var nextCollection = collection.Skip(1).ToList();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // construct the strings using yield return and recursionDi2015NewLine        foreach (var tail in GetStringCombinations(nextCollection))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            ls.add(letter + tail);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLinereturn ls;Di2015NewLine

6902665Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static class TypeBuilderHelperDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    /// <summary>Creates one constructor for each public constructor in the base class. Each constructor simplyDi2015NewLine    /// forwards its arguments to the base constructor, and matches the base constructor's signature.Di2015NewLine    /// Supports optional values, and custom attributes on constructors and parameters.Di2015NewLine    /// Does not support n-ary (variadic) constructors</summary>Di2015NewLine    public static void CreatePassThroughConstuctors(TypeBuilder builder, Type baseType)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        foreach (var constructor in baseType.GetConstructors()) {Di2015NewLine            var parameters = constructor.GetParameters();Di2015NewLine            if (parameters.Length > 0 && parameters.Last().IsDefined(typeof(ParamArrayAttribute), false)) {Di2015NewLine                //throw new InvalidOperationException("Variadic constructors are not supported");Di2015NewLine                continue;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            var parameterTypes = parameters.Select(p => p.ParameterType).ToArray();Di2015NewLine            var requiredCustomModifiers = parameters.Select(p => p.GetRequiredCustomModifiers()).ToArray();Di2015NewLine            var optionalCustomModifiers = parameters.Select(p => p.GetOptionalCustomModifiers()).ToArray();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            var ctor = builder.DefineConstructor(MethodAttributes.Public, constructor.CallingConvention, parameterTypes, requiredCustomModifiers, optionalCustomModifiers);Di2015NewLine            for (var i = 0; i < parameters.Length; ++i) {Di2015NewLine                var parameter = parameters[i];Di2015NewLine                var parameterBuilder = ctor.DefineParameter(i + 1, parameter.Attributes, parameter.Name);Di2015NewLine                if (((int)parameter.Attributes & (int)ParameterAttributes.HasDefault) != 0) {Di2015NewLine                    parameterBuilder.SetConstant(parameter.RawDefaultValue);Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                foreach (var attribute in BuildCustomAttributes(parameter.GetCustomAttributesData())) {Di2015NewLine                    parameterBuilder.SetCustomAttribute(attribute);Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            foreach (var attribute in BuildCustomAttributes(constructor.GetCustomAttributesData())) {Di2015NewLine                ctor.SetCustomAttribute(attribute);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            var emitter = ctor.GetILGenerator();Di2015NewLine            emitter.Emit(OpCodes.Nop);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // Load `this` and call base constructor with argumentsDi2015NewLine            emitter.Emit(OpCodes.Ldarg_0);Di2015NewLine            for (var i = 1; i <= parameters.Length; ++i) {Di2015NewLine                emitter.Emit(OpCodes.Ldarg, i);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            emitter.Emit(OpCodes.Call, constructor);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            emitter.Emit(OpCodes.Ret);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static CustomAttributeBuilder[] BuildCustomAttributes(IEnumerable<CustomAttributeData> customAttributes)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return customAttributes.Select(attribute => {Di2015NewLine            var attributeArgs = attribute.ConstructorArguments.Select(a => a.Value).ToArray();Di2015NewLine            var namedPropertyInfos = attribute.NamedArguments.Select(a => a.MemberInfo).OfType<PropertyInfo>().ToArray();Di2015NewLine            var namedPropertyValues = attribute.NamedArguments.Where(a => a.MemberInfo is PropertyInfo).Select(a => a.TypedValue.Value).ToArray();Di2015NewLine            var namedFieldInfos = attribute.NamedArguments.Select(a => a.MemberInfo).OfType<FieldInfo>().ToArray();Di2015NewLine            var namedFieldValues = attribute.NamedArguments.Where(a => a.MemberInfo is FieldInfo).Select(a => a.TypedValue.Value).ToArray();Di2015NewLine            return new CustomAttributeBuilder(attribute.Constructor, attributeArgs, namedPropertyInfos, namedPropertyValues, namedFieldInfos, namedFieldValues);Di2015NewLine        }).ToArray();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6905005Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static XDocument Load(XmlReader reader, LoadOptions options)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if (reader == null)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throw new ArgumentNullException("reader"); //ArgumentNullExceptionDi2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    if (reader.ReadState == ReadState.Initial)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        reader.Read();// Could throw XmlException according to MSDNDi2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    XDocument document = new XDocument();Di2015NewLine    if ((options & LoadOptions.SetBaseUri) != LoadOptions.None)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        string baseURI = reader.BaseURI;Di2015NewLine        if ((baseURI != null) && (baseURI.Length != 0))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            document.SetBaseUri(baseURI);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    if ((options & LoadOptions.SetLineInfo) != LoadOptions.None)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        IXmlLineInfo info = reader as IXmlLineInfo;Di2015NewLine        if ((info != null) && info.HasLineInfo())Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            document.SetLineInfo(info.LineNumber, info.LinePosition);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    if (reader.NodeType == XmlNodeType.XmlDeclaration)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        document.Declaration = new XDeclaration(reader);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    document.ReadContentFrom(reader, options); // InvalidOperationExceptionDi2015NewLine    if (!reader.EOF)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throw new InvalidOperationException(Res.GetString("InvalidOperation_ExpectedEndOfFile")); // InvalidOperationExceptionDi2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    if (document.Root == null)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throw new InvalidOperationException(Res.GetString("InvalidOperation_MissingRoot")); // InvalidOperationExceptionDi2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return document;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

static extern bool EndPagePrinter(IntPtr hPrinter);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  [DllImport("winspool.Drv", EntryPoint="WritePrinter", SetLastError=true, ExactSpelling=true, CallingConvention=CallingConvention.StdCall)]Di2015NewLine  public static extern bool WritePrinter(IntPtr hPrinter, IntPtr pBytes, Int32 dwCount, out Int32 dwWritten );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  // SendBytesToPrinter()Di2015NewLine  // When the function is given a printer name and an unmanaged arrayDi2015NewLine  // of bytes, the function sends those bytes to the print queue.Di2015NewLine  // Returns true on success, false on failure.Di2015NewLine  public static bool SendBytesToPrinter( string szPrinterName, IntPtr pBytes, Int32 dwCount)Di2015NewLine  {Di2015NewLine    Int32    dwError = 0, dwWritten = 0;Di2015NewLine    IntPtr    hPrinter = new IntPtr(0);Di2015NewLine    DOCINFOA    di = new DOCINFOA();Di2015NewLine    bool    bSuccess = false; // Assume failure unless you specifically succeed.Di2015NewLine    di.pDocName = "My C#.NET RAW Document";Di2015NewLine    di.pDataType = "RAW";Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Open the printer.Di2015NewLine    if( OpenPrinter( szPrinterName.Normalize(), out hPrinter, IntPtr.Zero ) )Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine      // Start a document.Di2015NewLine      if( StartDocPrinter(hPrinter, 1, di) )Di2015NewLine      {Di2015NewLine        // Start a page.Di2015NewLine        if( StartPagePrinter(hPrinter) )Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine          // Write your bytes.Di2015NewLine          bSuccess = WritePrinter(hPrinter, pBytes, dwCount, out dwWritten);Di2015NewLine          EndPagePrinter(hPrinter);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        EndDocPrinter(hPrinter);Di2015NewLine      }Di2015NewLine      ClosePrinter(hPrinter);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    // If you did not succeed, GetLastError may give more informationDi2015NewLine    // about why not.Di2015NewLine    if( bSuccess == false )Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine      dwError = Marshal.GetLastWin32Error();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return bSuccess;Di2015NewLine  }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  public static bool SendFileToPrinter( string szPrinterName, string szFileName )Di2015NewLine  {Di2015NewLine    // Open the file.Di2015NewLine    FileStream fs = new FileStream(szFileName, FileMode.Open);Di2015NewLine    // Create a BinaryReader on the file.Di2015NewLine    BinaryReader br = new BinaryReader(fs);Di2015NewLine    // Dim an array of bytes big enough to hold the file's contents.Di2015NewLine    Byte []bytes = new Byte[fs.Length];Di2015NewLine    bool bSuccess = false;Di2015NewLine    // Your unmanaged pointer.Di2015NewLine    IntPtr pUnmanagedBytes = new IntPtr(0);Di2015NewLine    int nLength;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    nLength = Convert.ToInt32(fs.Length);Di2015NewLine    // Read the contents of the file into the array.Di2015NewLine    bytes = br.ReadBytes( nLength );Di2015NewLine    // Allocate some unmanaged memory for those bytes.Di2015NewLine    pUnmanagedBytes = Marshal.AllocCoTaskMem(nLength);Di2015NewLine    // Copy the managed byte array into the unmanaged array.Di2015NewLine    Marshal.Copy(bytes, 0, pUnmanagedBytes, nLength);Di2015NewLine    // Send the unmanaged bytes to the printer.Di2015NewLine    bSuccess = SendBytesToPrinter(szPrinterName, pUnmanagedBytes, nLength);Di2015NewLine    // Free the unmanaged memory that you allocated earlier.Di2015NewLine    Marshal.FreeCoTaskMem(pUnmanagedBytes);Di2015NewLine    return bSuccess;Di2015NewLine  }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  public static bool SendStringToPrinter( string szPrinterName, string szString )Di2015NewLine  {Di2015NewLine    IntPtr pBytes;Di2015NewLine    Int32 dwCount;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // How many characters are in the string?Di2015NewLine    // Fix from Nicholas Piasecki:Di2015NewLine    // dwCount = szString.Length;Di2015NewLine    dwCount = (szString.Length + 1) * Marshal.SystemMaxDBCSCharSize;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Assume that the printer is expecting ANSI text, and then convertDi2015NewLine    // the string to ANSI text.Di2015NewLine    pBytes = Marshal.StringToCoTaskMemAnsi(szString);Di2015NewLine    // Send the converted ANSI string to the printer.Di2015NewLine    SendBytesToPrinter(szPrinterName, pBytes, dwCount);Di2015NewLine    Marshal.FreeCoTaskMem(pBytes);Di2015NewLine    return true;Di2015NewLine  }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6914197Di2015UniqueSeparatorWebClient.DownloadFileAsync
6914197Di2015UniqueSeparatorDownloadProgressChanged
6914197Di2015UniqueSeparatorDownloadFileCompleted
6914197Di2015UniqueSeparatorBlockingCollection
6914197Di2015UniqueSeparator// Information used in callbacks.Di2015NewLineclass DownloadArgsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    public readonly string Url;Di2015NewLine    public readonly string Filename;Di2015NewLine    public readonly WebClient Client;Di2015NewLine    public DownloadArgs(string u, string f, WebClient c)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        Url = u;Di2015NewLine        Filename = f;Di2015NewLine        Client = c;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineconst int MaxClients = 4;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// create a queue that allows the max itemsDi2015NewLineBlockingCollection<WebClient> ClientQueue = new BlockingCollection<WebClient>(MaxClients);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// queue of urls to be downloaded (unbounded)Di2015NewLineQueue<string> UrlQueue = new Queue<string>();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// create four WebClient instances and put them into the queueDi2015NewLinefor (int i = 0; i < MaxClients; ++i)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    var cli = new WebClient();Di2015NewLine    cli.DownloadProgressChanged += DownloadProgressChanged;Di2015NewLine    cli.DownloadFileCompleted += DownloadFileCompleted;Di2015NewLine    ClientQueue.Add(cli);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Fill the UrlQueue hereDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Now go until the UrlQueue is emptyDi2015NewLinewhile (UrlQueue.Count > 0)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    WebClient cli = ClientQueue.Take(); // blocks if there is no client availableDi2015NewLine    string url = UrlQueue.Dequeue();Di2015NewLine    string fname = CreateOutputFilename(url);  // or however you get the output file nameDi2015NewLine    cli.DownloadFileAsync(new Uri(url), fname, Di2015NewLine        new DownloadArgs(url, fname, cli));Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLinevoid DownloadProgressChanged(object sender, DownloadProgressChangedEventArgs e)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    DownloadArgs args = (DownloadArgs)e.UserState;Di2015NewLine    // Do status updates for this downloadDi2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinevoid DownloadFileCompleted(object sender, AsyncCompletedEventArgs e)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    DownloadArgs args = (DownloadArgs)e.UserState;Di2015NewLine    // do whatever UI updatesDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // now put this client back into the queueDi2015NewLine    ClientQueue.Add(args.Client);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

6916541Di2015UniqueSeparatorclass ProgramDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    static void Main( string[] args )Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // Test driver - create a Wedge, convert to Bitmap, save to fileDi2015NewLine        //Di2015NewLine        int width = 4095;Di2015NewLine        int height = 1200;Di2015NewLine        int bits = 12;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        byte[] wedge = Wedge( width, height, bits );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        Bitmap bmp = Convert( wedge, width, height, bits );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        string file = "wedge.png";Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        bmp.Save( file );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        Process.Start( file );Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    static Bitmap Convert( byte[] input, int width, int height, int bits )Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // Convert byte buffer (2 bytes per pixel) to 32-bit ARGB bitmapDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        var bitmap = new Bitmap( width, height, PixelFormat.Format32bppArgb );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        var rect = new Rectangle( 0, 0, width, height );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        var lut = CreateLut( bits );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        var bitmap_data = bitmap.LockBits( rect, ImageLockMode.WriteOnly, bitmap.PixelFormat );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        ConvertCore( width, height, bits, input, bitmap_data, lut );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        bitmap.UnlockBits( bitmap_data );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return bitmap;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    static unsafe void ConvertCore( int width, int height, int bits, byte[] input, BitmapData output, uint[] lut )Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // Copy pixels from input to output, applying LUTDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        ushort mask = (ushort)( ( 1 << bits ) - 1 );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        int in_stride = output.Stride;Di2015NewLine        int out_stride = width * 2;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        byte* out_data = (byte*)output.Scan0;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        fixed ( byte* in_data = input )Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            for ( int y = 0; y < height; y++ )Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                uint* out_row = (uint*)( out_data + ( y * in_stride ) );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                ushort* in_row = (ushort*)( in_data + ( y * out_stride ) );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                for ( int x = 0; x < width; x++ )Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    ushort in_pixel = (ushort)( in_row[ x ] & mask );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    out_row[ x ] = lut[ in_pixel ];Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    static uint[] CreateLut( int bits )Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // Create a linear LUT to convert from grayscale to ARGBDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        int max_input = 1 << bits;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        uint[] lut = new uint[ max_input ];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for ( int i = 0; i < max_input; i++ )Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            // map input value to 8-bit rangeDi2015NewLine            //Di2015NewLine            byte intensity = (byte)( ( i * 0xFF ) / max_input );Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // create ARGB output value A=255, R=G=B=intensityDi2015NewLine            //Di2015NewLine            lut[ i ] = (uint)( 0xFF000000L | ( intensity * 0x00010101L ) );Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return lut;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    static byte[] Wedge( int width, int height, int bits )Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // horizontal wedgeDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        int max = 1 << bits;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        byte[] pixels = new byte[ width * height * 2 ];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for ( int y = 0; y < height; y++ )Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            for ( int x = 0; x < width; x++ )Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                int pixel = x % max;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                int addr = ( ( y * width ) + x ) * 2;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                pixels[ addr + 1 ] = (byte)( ( pixel & 0xFF00 ) >> 8 );Di2015NewLine                pixels[ addr + 0 ] = (byte)( ( pixel & 0x00FF ) );Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return pixels;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine
